# Acceptance-command allowlist (ADR-014). One bare command name per line.
#
# Entries here EXECUTE REPOSITORY CODE at `done` time inside the closing
# session -- that is their purpose. This list is deliberately separate
# from .truth/evidence-allow (ADR-009), which must stay read-only:
# reusing it would force an unsafe override on every real oracle and
# teach the gate's own bypass.
#
# The structural screen still applies: no command substitution,
# pipelines only of listed entries, output redirection only to /dev/null
# or an fd dup. Programs are bare listed names -- OR (issue #7, v0.7.2)
# an EXACT repo-relative path listed here (.venv/bin/python, ./gradlew):
# a committed exact path bounds precisely which executable runs, which
# is stronger than an interpreter bare-name. Absolute paths and '..'
# segments never pass.
#
# The template ships this list EMPTY: which programs a work item may
# cause a later session to run is a per-repository policy decision.
# Typical conscious additions:
#
#   pytest        # suite oracle (verification)
#   python3       # golden-diff runners: python3 exercises/.../runner.py
#   bash          # gate scripts: bash scripts/spec-health.sh
#   make          # make test
#   npm           # npm test
#   cargo         # cargo test
#
# Note that an interpreter entry (python3, bash) admits ANY repo script
# as an oracle -- that breadth is usually the point, but it is a policy
# you are accepting, not a default you inherited.
